    "en": {
      "title": "In \u201cKota Ko Kama\u201d Rs. 4.5 crore foreign funds",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Police said that the Criminal Investigation Department has started investigations regarding the receipt of large amount of funds from foreign countries to the three leading activists of the 'Kota Ko Kama' protest site located in Galle Mukhatidadal.",
        "Police Media Spokesperson Senior Superintendent of Police Nihal Talduwa said that the Criminal Investigation Department is currently investigating the incident.",
        "Ratthu Senaratne, Thilan Senanayake and Avishka Viraj Konara, known as Ratta, opened three new accounts at Bank of Sri Lanka's Union Place branch last week.",
        "According to the police, 45 million rupees have been deposited from abroad in these three accounts.",
        "According to reports, after a few hours, they allegedly came to the bank, recovered the entire amount and threatened the bank officials who inquired about the reason for the withdrawal."
      ],
